{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c2e40f20-5af1-470e-a0e8-4598fda8fcc4","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly how to convert your page and catch errors at build time.\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage`:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Slider Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe only change needed is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` (adjust namespace)\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the `ContentPage`\n\nYour existing `{Binding ...}` markup stays the same — the XAML compiler now resolves them at compile time.\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time:**\n\nIn your `.csproj`, ensure this is set (it's on by default in .NET 8+ MAUI):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treats invalid compiled bindings as build errors -->\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, if you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **compile-time error** like:\n\n> `XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"`\n\n**Key points:**\n- `x:DataType` can also be set on child elements to scope to a different type (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`).\n- To opt out for a specific binding (e.g., when the type varies at runtime), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally or switch to `{Binding Path=..., x:DataType={x:Null}}`.\n- Compiled bindings also improve performance by avoiding runtime reflection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"192300f8-c574-4bab-a349-5be109b27a6d","outputTokens":607,"requestId":"3C35:16C73:D29758:1063A79:6A0128BC"},"id":"54f0128a-eb6e-4e47-8d92-23a260b29cdb","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:54:34.046Z","parentId":"197f207f-0fd2-4c4b-ad5b-79623aa5a1e3"}
